==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|translatio|trānslātiō|transfer|lang=la}}, from {{term|trans-||across|lang=la}}, + {{term|latio|lātiō|carrying|lang=la}}, from {{term|latus|lātus|lang=la}}, perfect passive participle of irregular verb {{term|fero|ferō|lang=la}} (compare '''[[transfer]]'''), + noun of action suffix {{term|-io|-iō|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{audio|En-us-translation.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{IPA|/trænz'leɪʃən/}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|s|-}}

# {{uncountable}} The act of converting or [[translate|translating]] (text from one [[language]] to another).
# {{countable}} The end result of translating text.
# {{physics}} Translation of forces in a gearbox.  <!--needs a proper definition-->
# {{countable}} {{context|mathematics|physics}} Motion of a body on a linear path, without deformation or rotation, ''i.e.'' such that every part of the body moves at the same speed and in the same direction.
# {{genetics}} A process occurring in the ribosome, in which a strand of messenger RNA (mRNA) guides assembly of a sequence of [[amino acid|amino acids]] to make a [[protein]].

